						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up in the temple of Durgā-Paramēśvari.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṁghaṇa—A.D. 1236.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">26th year</hi> of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Siṁghaṇadēva, Manmatha, ba. 10, Tuesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1236, March 4, Tuesday.</hi> The month, which is omitted, was <hi rend="bold">Phālguṇa</hi> as is known from other records mentioning the same incident and bearing the same date. It records the death of <hi rend="bold">Sōvabōva</hi> in an attack on <hi rend="bold">Ajaḍi</hi> by <hi rend="bold">Pōḍiyadēva (Pāṇḍyadēva ?).</hi></p>						

						</summary>
